208inline void BuilderCustom::resetEffectiveZoom(BuilderState& builderState)
209{
210 // Reset the zoom in effect. This allows the setZoom method to accurately compute a new zoom in effect.
211 builderState.setEffectiveZoom(builderState.parentStyle().effectiveZoom());
212}

214inline void BuilderCustom::applyInitialZoom(BuilderState& builderState)
215{
216 resetEffectiveZoom(builderState);
217 builderState.setZoom(RenderStyle::initialZoom());
218}

220inline void BuilderCustom::applyInheritZoom(BuilderState& builderState)
221{
222 resetEffectiveZoom(builderState);

225
226inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueZoom(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
227{
228 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
229
230 if (primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueNormal) {
231 resetEffectiveZoom(builderState);
232 builderState.setZoom(RenderStyle::initialZoom());
233 } else if (primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueReset) {
234 builderState.setEffectiveZoom(RenderStyle::initialZoom());
235 builderState.setZoom(RenderStyle::initialZoom());
236 } else if (primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueDocument) {
237 float docZoom = builderState.rootElementStyle() ? builderState.rootElementStyle()->zoom() : RenderStyle::initialZoom();
238 builderState.setEffectiveZoom(docZoom);
239 builderState.setZoom(docZoom);
240 } else if (primitiveValue.isPercentage()) {
241 resetEffectiveZoom(builderState);
242 if (float percent = primitiveValue.floatValue())
243 builderState.setZoom(percent / 100.0f);
244 } else if (primitiveValue.isNumber()) {
245 resetEffectiveZoom(builderState);
246 if (float number = primitiveValue.floatValue())
247 builderState.setZoom(number);
248 }

260bool BuilderCustom::getPageSizeFromName(CSSPrimitiveValue* pageSizeName, CSSPrimitiveValue* pageOrientation, Length& width, Length& height)
261{
262 static NeverDestroyed<Length> a5Width(mmLength(148));
263 static NeverDestroyed<Length> a5Height(mmLength(210));
264 static NeverDestroyed<Length> a4Width(mmLength(210));
265 static NeverDestroyed<Length> a4Height(mmLength(297));
266 static NeverDestroyed<Length> a3Width(mmLength(297));
267 static NeverDestroyed<Length> a3Height(mmLength(420));
268 static NeverDestroyed<Length> b5Width(mmLength(176));
269 static NeverDestroyed<Length> b5Height(mmLength(250));
270 static NeverDestroyed<Length> b4Width(mmLength(250));
271 static NeverDestroyed<Length> b4Height(mmLength(353));
272 static NeverDestroyed<Length> letterWidth(inchLength(8.5));
273 static NeverDestroyed<Length> letterHeight(inchLength(11));
274 static NeverDestroyed<Length> legalWidth(inchLength(8.5));
275 static NeverDestroyed<Length> legalHeight(inchLength(14));
276 static NeverDestroyed<Length> ledgerWidth(inchLength(11));
277 static NeverDestroyed<Length> ledgerHeight(inchLength(17));
278
279 if (!pageSizeName)
280 return false;
281
282 switch (pageSizeName->valueID()) {
283 case CSSValueA5:
284 width = a5Width;
285 height = a5Height;
286 break;
287 case CSSValueA4:
288 width = a4Width;
289 height = a4Height;
290 break;
291 case CSSValueA3:
292 width = a3Width;
293 height = a3Height;
294 break;
295 case CSSValueB5:
296 width = b5Width;
297 height = b5Height;
298 break;
299 case CSSValueB4:
300 width = b4Width;
301 height = b4Height;
302 break;
303 case CSSValueLetter:
304 width = letterWidth;
305 height = letterHeight;
306 break;
307 case CSSValueLegal:
308 width = legalWidth;
309 height = legalHeight;
310 break;
311 case CSSValueLedger:
312 width = ledgerWidth;
313 height = ledgerHeight;
314 break;
315 default:
316 return false;
317 }
318
319 if (pageOrientation) {
320 switch (pageOrientation->valueID()) {
321 case CSSValueLandscape:
322 std::swap(width, height);
323 break;
324 case CSSValuePortrait:
325 // Nothing to do.
326 break;
327 default:
328 return false;
329 }
330 }
331 return true;
332}

365inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueImageResolution(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
366{
367 ImageResolutionSource source = RenderStyle::initialImageResolutionSource();
368 ImageResolutionSnap snap = RenderStyle::initialImageResolutionSnap();
369 double resolution = RenderStyle::initialImageResolution();
370 for (auto& item : downcast<CSSValueList>(value)) {
371 CSSPrimitiveValue& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get());
372 if (primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueFromImage)
373 source = ImageResolutionSource::FromImage;
374 else if (primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueSnap)
375 snap = ImageResolutionSnap::Pixels;
376 else
377 resolution = primitiveValue.doubleValue(CSSUnitType::CSS_DPPX);
378 }
379 builderState.style().setImageResolutionSource(source);
380 builderState.style().setImageResolutionSnap(snap);
381 builderState.style().setImageResolution(resolution);
382}

390inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueSize(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
391{
392 builderState.style().resetPageSizeType();
393
394 if (!is<CSSValueList>(value))
395 return;
396
397 Length width;
398 Length height;
399 PageSizeType pageSizeType = PAGE_SIZE_AUTO;
400
401 auto& valueList = downcast<CSSValueList>(value);
402 switch (valueList.length()) {
403 case 2: {
404 auto firstValue = valueList.itemWithoutBoundsCheck(0);
405 auto secondValue = valueList.itemWithoutBoundsCheck(1);
406 // <length>{2} | <page-size> <orientation>
407 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*firstValue) || !is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*secondValue))
408 return;
409 auto& firstPrimitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*firstValue);
410 auto& secondPrimitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*secondValue);
411 if (firstPrimitiveValue.isLength()) {
412 // <length>{2}
413 if (!secondPrimitiveValue.isLength())
414 return;
415 CSSToLengthConversionData conversionData = builderState.cssToLengthConversionData().copyWithAdjustedZoom(1.0f);
416 width = firstPrimitiveValue.computeLength<Length>(conversionData);
417 height = secondPrimitiveValue.computeLength<Length>(conversionData);
418 } else {
419 // <page-size> <orientation>
420 // The value order is guaranteed. See CSSParser::parseSizeParameter.
421 if (!getPageSizeFromName(&firstPrimitiveValue, &secondPrimitiveValue, width, height))
422 return;
423 }
424 pageSizeType = PAGE_SIZE_RESOLVED;
425 break;
426 }
427 case 1: {
428 auto value = valueList.itemWithoutBoundsCheck(0);
429 // <length> | auto | <page-size> | [ portrait | landscape]
430 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*value))
431 return;
432 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*value);
433 if (primitiveValue.isLength()) {
434 // <length>
435 pageSizeType = PAGE_SIZE_RESOLVED;
436 width = height = primitiveValue.computeLength<Length>(builderState.cssToLengthConversionData().copyWithAdjustedZoom(1.0f));
437 } else {
438 switch (primitiveValue.valueID()) {
439 case 0:
440 return;
441 case CSSValueAuto:
442 pageSizeType = PAGE_SIZE_AUTO;
443 break;
444 case CSSValuePortrait:
445 pageSizeType = PAGE_SIZE_AUTO_PORTRAIT;
446 break;
447 case CSSValueLandscape:
448 pageSizeType = PAGE_SIZE_AUTO_LANDSCAPE;
449 break;
450 default:
451 // <page-size>
452 pageSizeType = PAGE_SIZE_RESOLVED;
453 if (!getPageSizeFromName(&primitiveValue, nullptr, width, height))
454 return;
455 }
456 }
457 break;
458 }
459 default:
460 return;
461 }
462 builderState.style().setPageSizeType(pageSizeType);
463 builderState.style().setPageSize({ WTFMove(width), WTFMove(height) });
464}

480inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueTextIndent(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
481{
482 Length lengthOrPercentageValue;
483 TextIndentLine textIndentLineValue = RenderStyle::initialTextIndentLine();
484 TextIndentType textIndentTypeValue = RenderStyle::initialTextIndentType();
485 for (auto& item : downcast<CSSValueList>(value)) {
486 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get());
487 if (!primitiveValue.valueID())
488 lengthOrPercentageValue = primitiveValue.convertToLength<FixedIntegerConversion | PercentConversion | CalculatedConversion>(builderState.cssToLengthConversionData());
489 else if (primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueEachLine)
490 textIndentLineValue = TextIndentLine::EachLine;
491 else if (primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueHanging)
492 textIndentTypeValue = TextIndentType::Hanging;
493 }
494
495 if (lengthOrPercentageValue.isUndefined())
496 return;
497
498 builderState.style().setTextIndent(WTFMove(lengthOrPercentageValue));
499 builderState.style().setTextIndentLine(textIndentLineValue);
500 builderState.style().setTextIndentType(textIndentTypeValue);
501}

503enum BorderImageType { BorderImage, WebkitMaskBoxImage };
504enum BorderImageModifierType { Outset, Repeat, Slice, Width };
505template <BorderImageType type, BorderImageModifierType modifier>
506class ApplyPropertyBorderImageModifier {
507public:
508 static void applyInheritValue(BuilderState& builderState)
509 {
510 NinePieceImage image(getValue(builderState.style()));
511 switch (modifier) {
512 case Outset:
513 image.copyOutsetFrom(getValue(builderState.parentStyle()));
514 break;
515 case Repeat:
516 image.copyRepeatFrom(getValue(builderState.parentStyle()));
517 break;
518 case Slice:
519 image.copyImageSlicesFrom(getValue(builderState.parentStyle()));
520 break;
521 case Width:
522 image.copyBorderSlicesFrom(getValue(builderState.parentStyle()));
523 break;
524 }
525 setValue(builderState.style(), image);
526 }
527
528 static void applyInitialValue(BuilderState& builderState)
529 {
530 NinePieceImage image(getValue(builderState.style()));
531 switch (modifier) {
532 case Outset:
533 image.setOutset(LengthBox(LengthType::Relative));
534 break;
535 case Repeat:
536 image.setHorizontalRule(NinePieceImageRule::Stretch);
537 image.setVerticalRule(NinePieceImageRule::Stretch);
538 break;
539 case Slice:
540 // Masks have a different initial value for slices. Preserve the value of "0 fill" for backwards compatibility.
541 image.setImageSlices(type == BorderImage ? LengthBox(Length(100, LengthType::Percent), Length(100, LengthType::Percent), Length(100, LengthType::Percent), Length(100, LengthType::Percent)) : LengthBox());
542 image.setFill(type != BorderImage);
543 break;
544 case Width:
545 // FIXME: This is a local variable to work around a bug in the GCC 8.1 Address Sanitizer.
546 // Might be slightly less efficient when the type is not BorderImage since this is unused in that case.
547 // Should be switched back to a temporary when possible. See https://webkit.org/b/186980
548 LengthBox lengthBox(Length(1, LengthType::Relative), Length(1, LengthType::Relative), Length(1, LengthType::Relative), Length(1, LengthType::Relative));
549 // Masks have a different initial value for widths. They use an 'auto' value rather than trying to fit to the border.
550 image.setBorderSlices(type == BorderImage ? lengthBox : LengthBox());
551 break;
552 }
553 setValue(builderState.style(), image);
554 }
555
556 static void applyValue(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
557 {
558 NinePieceImage image(getValue(builderState.style()));
559 switch (modifier) {
560 case Outset:
561 image.setOutset(builderState.styleMap().mapNinePieceImageQuad(value));
562 break;
563 case Repeat:
564 builderState.styleMap().mapNinePieceImageRepeat(value, image);
565 break;
566 case Slice:
567 builderState.styleMap().mapNinePieceImageSlice(value, image);
568 break;
569 case Width:
570 image.setBorderSlices(builderState.styleMap().mapNinePieceImageQuad(value));
571 break;
572 }
573 setValue(builderState.style(), image);
574 }
575
576private:
577 static const NinePieceImage& getValue(const RenderStyle& style)
578 {
579 return type == BorderImage ? style.borderImage() : style.maskBoxImage();
580 }
581
582 static void setValue(RenderStyle& style, const NinePieceImage& value)
583 {
584 return type == BorderImage ? style.setBorderImage(value) : style.setMaskBoxImage(value);
585 }
586};
587
588#define DEFINE_BORDER_IMAGE_MODIFIER_HANDLER(type, modifier) \
589inline void BuilderCustom::applyInherit##type##modifier(BuilderState& builderState) \
590{ \
591 ApplyPropertyBorderImageModifier<type, modifier>::applyInheritValue(builderState); \
592} \
593inline void BuilderCustom::applyInitial##type##modifier(BuilderState& builderState) \
594{ \
595 ApplyPropertyBorderImageModifier<type, modifier>::applyInitialValue(builderState); \
596} \
597inline void BuilderCustom::applyValue##type##modifier(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value) \
598{ \
599 ApplyPropertyBorderImageModifier<type, modifier>::applyValue(builderState, value); \
600}

602DEFINE_BORDER_IMAGE_MODIFIER_HANDLER(BorderImage, Outset)
603DEFINE_BORDER_IMAGE_MODIFIER_HANDLER(BorderImage, Repeat)

611static inline void applyLetterSpacing(BuilderState& builderState, float letterSpacing)
612{
613 // Setting the letter-spacing from a positive value to another positive value shouldn't require fonts to get updated.
614
615 bool shouldDisableLigaturesForSpacing = letterSpacing;
616 if (shouldDisableLigaturesForSpacing != builderState.fontDescription().shouldDisableLigaturesForSpacing()) {
617 auto fontDescription = builderState.fontDescription();
618 fontDescription.setShouldDisableLigaturesForSpacing(letterSpacing);
619 builderState.setFontDescription(WTFMove(fontDescription));
620 }
621
622 builderState.style().setLetterSpacingWithoutUpdatingFontDescription(letterSpacing);
623}
624
625inline void BuilderCustom::applyInheritLetterSpacing(BuilderState& builderState)
626{
627 applyLetterSpacing(builderState, builderState.parentStyle().letterSpacing());
628}
629
630inline void BuilderCustom::applyInitialLetterSpacing(BuilderState& builderState)
631{
632 applyLetterSpacing(builderState, RenderStyle::initialLetterSpacing());
633}
634
635void maybeUpdateFontForLetterSpacing(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
636{
637 // This is unfortunate. It's related to https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/5498.
638 //
639 // From StyleBuilder's point of view, there's a dependency cycle:
640 // letter-spacing accepts an arbitrary <length>, which must be resolved against a font, which must
641 // be selected after all the properties that affect font selection are processed, but letter-spacing
642 // itself affects font selection because it can disable font features. StyleBuilder has some (valid)
643 // ASSERT()s which would fire because of this cycle.
644 //
645 // There isn't *actually* a dependency cycle, though, as none of the font-relative units are
646 // actually sensitive to font features (luckily). The problem is that our StyleBuilder is only
647 // smart enough to consider fonts as one indivisible thing, rather than having the deeper
648 // understanding that different parts of fonts may or may not depend on each other.
649 //
650 // So, we update the font early here, so that if there is a font-relative unit inside the CSSValue,
651 // its font is updated and ready to go. In the worst case there might be a second call to
652 // updateFont() later, but that isn't bad for perf because 1. It only happens twice if there is
653 // actually a font-relative unit passed to letter-spacing, and 2. updateFont() internally has logic
654 // to only do work if the font is actually dirty.
655
656 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value)) {
657 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
658 if (primitiveValue.isFontRelativeLength() || primitiveValue.isCalculated())
659 builderState.updateFont();
660 }
661}
662
663inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueLetterSpacing(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
664{
665 maybeUpdateFontForLetterSpacing(builderState, value);
666 applyLetterSpacing(builderState, BuilderConverter::convertSpacing(builderState, value));
667}

683static inline float computeBaseSpecifiedFontSize(const Document& document, const RenderStyle& style, bool percentageAutosizingEnabled)
684{
685 float result = style.specifiedFontSize();
686 auto* frame = document.frame();
687 if (frame && style.textZoom() != TextZoom::Reset)
688 result *= frame->textZoomFactor();
689 result *= style.effectiveZoom();
690 if (percentageAutosizingEnabled
691 && (!document.settings().textAutosizingUsesIdempotentMode() || document.settings().idempotentModeAutosizingOnlyHonorsPercentages()))
692 result *= style.textSizeAdjust().multiplier();
693 return result;
694}
695
696static inline float computeLineHeightMultiplierDueToFontSize(const Document& document, const RenderStyle& style, const CSSPrimitiveValue& value)
697{
698 bool percentageAutosizingEnabled = document.settings().textAutosizingEnabled() && style.textSizeAdjust().isPercentage();
699
700 if (value.isLength()) {
701 auto minimumFontSize = document.settings().minimumFontSize();
702 if (minimumFontSize > 0) {
703 auto specifiedFontSize = computeBaseSpecifiedFontSize(document, style, percentageAutosizingEnabled);
704 // Small font sizes cause a preposterously large (near infinity) line-height. Add a fuzz-factor of 1px which opts out of
705 // boosted line-height.
706 if (specifiedFontSize < minimumFontSize && specifiedFontSize >= 1) {
707 // FIXME: There are two settings which are relevant here: minimum font size, and minimum logical font size (as
708 // well as things like the zoom property, text zoom on the page, and text autosizing). The minimum logical font
709 // size is nonzero by default, and already incorporated into the computed font size, so if we just use the ratio
710 // of the computed : specified font size, it will be > 1 in the cases where the minimum logical font size kicks
711 // in. In general, this is the right thing to do, however, this kind of blanket change is too risky to perform
712 // right now. https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=174570 tracks turning this on. For now, we can just pretend
713 // that the minimum font size is the only thing affecting the computed font size.
714
715 // This calculation matches the line-height computed size calculation in
716 // TextAutoSizing::Value::adjustTextNodeSizes().
717 auto scaleChange = minimumFontSize / specifiedFontSize;
718 return scaleChange;
719 }
720 }
721 }
722
723 if (percentageAutosizingEnabled && !document.settings().textAutosizingUsesIdempotentMode())
724 return style.textSizeAdjust().multiplier();
725 return 1;
726}

728inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueLineHeight(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
729{
730 std::optional<Length> lineHeight = BuilderConverter::convertLineHeight(builderState, value, 1);
731 if (!lineHeight)
732 return;
733
734 Length computedLineHeight;
735 if (lineHeight.value().isNegative())
736 computedLineHeight = lineHeight.value();
737 else {
738 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
739 auto multiplier = computeLineHeightMultiplierDueToFontSize(builderState.document(), builderState.style(), primitiveValue);
740 if (multiplier == 1)
741 computedLineHeight = lineHeight.value();
742 else
743 computedLineHeight = BuilderConverter::convertLineHeight(builderState, value, multiplier).value();
744 }
745
746 builderState.style().setLineHeight(WTFMove(computedLineHeight));
747 builderState.style().setSpecifiedLineHeight(WTFMove(lineHeight.value()));
748}

932template<CSSPropertyID property>
933inline void BuilderCustom::applyTextOrBoxShadowValue(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
934{
935 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value)) {
936 ASSERT(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value).valueID() == CSSValueNone);
937 if (property == CSSPropertyTextShadow)
938 builderState.style().setTextShadow(nullptr);
939 else
940 builderState.style().setBoxShadow(nullptr);
941 return;
942 }
943
944 bool isFirstEntry = true;
945 for (auto& item : downcast<CSSValueList>(value)) {
946 auto& shadowValue = downcast<CSSShadowValue>(item.get());
947 auto conversionData = builderState.cssToLengthConversionData();
948 auto x = shadowValue.x->computeLength<LayoutUnit>(conversionData);
949 auto y = shadowValue.y->computeLength<LayoutUnit>(conversionData);
950 int blur = shadowValue.blur ? shadowValue.blur->computeLength<int>(conversionData) : 0;
951 auto spread = shadowValue.spread ? shadowValue.spread->computeLength<LayoutUnit>(conversionData) : LayoutUnit(0);
952 ShadowStyle shadowStyle = shadowValue.style && shadowValue.style->valueID() == CSSValueInset ? ShadowStyle::Inset : ShadowStyle::Normal;
953 Color color;
954 if (shadowValue.color)
955 color = builderState.colorFromPrimitiveValueWithResolvedCurrentColor(*shadowValue.color);
956 else
957 color = builderState.style().color();
958
959 auto shadowData = makeUnique<ShadowData>(LayoutPoint(x, y), blur, spread, shadowStyle, property == CSSPropertyWebkitBoxShadow, color.isValid() ? color : Color::transparentBlack);
960 if (property == CSSPropertyTextShadow)
961 builderState.style().setTextShadow(WTFMove(shadowData), !isFirstEntry); // add to the list if this is not the first entry
962 else
963 builderState.style().setBoxShadow(WTFMove(shadowData), !isFirstEntry); // add to the list if this is not the first entry
964 isFirstEntry = false;
965 }
966}

1013inline void BuilderCustom::applyInitialFontFamily(BuilderState& builderState)
1014{
1015 auto fontDescription = builderState.fontDescription();
1016 auto initialDesc = FontCascadeDescription();
1017
1018 // We need to adjust the size to account for the generic family change from monospace to non-monospace.
1019 if (fontDescription.useFixedDefaultSize()) {
1020 if (CSSValueID sizeIdentifier = fontDescription.keywordSizeAsIdentifier())
1021 builderState.setFontSize(fontDescription, Style::fontSizeForKeyword(sizeIdentifier, false, builderState.document()));
1022 }
1023 if (!initialDesc.firstFamily().isEmpty())
1024 fontDescription.setFamilies(initialDesc.families());
1025
1026 builderState.setFontDescription(WTFMove(fontDescription));
1027}

1038
1039inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueFontFamily(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1040{
1041 auto& valueList = downcast<CSSValueList>(value);
1042
1043 auto fontDescription = builderState.fontDescription();
1044 // Before mapping in a new font-family property, we should reset the generic family.
1045 bool oldFamilyUsedFixedDefaultSize = fontDescription.useFixedDefaultSize();
1046
1047 Vector<AtomString> families;
1048 families.reserveInitialCapacity(valueList.length());
1049
1050 for (auto& item : valueList) {
1051 auto& contentValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get());
1052 AtomString family;
1053 bool isGenericFamily = false;
1054 if (contentValue.isFontFamily()) {
1055 const CSSFontFamily& fontFamily = contentValue.fontFamily();
1056 family = fontFamily.familyName;
1057 // If the family name was resolved by the CSS parser from a system font ID, then it is generic.
1058 isGenericFamily = fontFamily.fromSystemFontID;
1059 } else {
1060 if (contentValue.valueID() == CSSValueWebkitBody)
1061 family = builderState.document().settings().standardFontFamily();
1062 else {
1063 isGenericFamily = true;
1064 family = CSSPropertyParserHelpers::genericFontFamily(contentValue.valueID());
1065 }
1066 }
1067
1068 if (family.isEmpty())
1069 continue;
1070 if (families.isEmpty())
1071 fontDescription.setIsSpecifiedFont(!isGenericFamily);
1072 families.uncheckedAppend(family);
1073 }
1074
1075 if (families.isEmpty())
1076 return;
1077 fontDescription.setFamilies(families);
1078
1079 if (fontDescription.useFixedDefaultSize() != oldFamilyUsedFixedDefaultSize) {
1080 if (CSSValueID sizeIdentifier = fontDescription.keywordSizeAsIdentifier())
1081 builderState.setFontSize(fontDescription, Style::fontSizeForKeyword(sizeIdentifier, !oldFamilyUsedFixedDefaultSize, builderState.document()));
1082 }
1083
1084 builderState.setFontDescription(WTFMove(fontDescription));
1085}

1166inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueBaselineShift(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1167{
1168 SVGRenderStyle& svgStyle = builderState.style().accessSVGStyle();
1169 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
1170 if (primitiveValue.isValueID()) {
1171 switch (primitiveValue.valueID()) {
1172 case CSSValueBaseline:
1173 svgStyle.setBaselineShift(BaselineShift::Baseline);
1174 break;
1175 case CSSValueSub:
1176 svgStyle.setBaselineShift(BaselineShift::Sub);
1177 break;
1178 case CSSValueSuper:
1179 svgStyle.setBaselineShift(BaselineShift::Super);
1180 break;
1181 default:
1182 break;
1183 }
1184 } else {
1185 svgStyle.setBaselineShift(BaselineShift::Length);
1186 svgStyle.setBaselineShiftValue(SVGLengthValue::fromCSSPrimitiveValue(primitiveValue));
1187 }
1188}

1214inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueAspectRatio(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1215{
1216 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value)) {
1217 ASSERT(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value).valueID() == CSSValueAuto);
1218 return builderState.style().setAspectRatioType(AspectRatioType::Auto);
1219 }
1220
1221 if (!is<CSSValueList>(value))
1222 return;
1223
1224 auto& list = downcast<CSSValueList>(value);
1225 if (list.item(1)->isValueList()) {
1226 builderState.style().setAspectRatioType(AspectRatioType::AutoAndRatio);
1227 auto ratioList = downcast<CSSValueList>(list.item(1));
1228 ASSERT(ratioList->length() == 2);
1229 builderState.style().setAspectRatio(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(ratioList->item(0))->doubleValue(), downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(ratioList->item(1))->doubleValue());
1230 return;
1231 }
1232
1233 ASSERT(list.length() == 2);
1234 auto width = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(list.item(0))->doubleValue();
1235 auto height = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(list.item(1))->doubleValue();
1236 if (!width || !height)
1237 builderState.style().setAspectRatioType(AspectRatioType::AutoZero);
1238 else
1239 builderState.style().setAspectRatioType(AspectRatioType::Ratio);
1240 builderState.style().setAspectRatio(width, height);
1241}

1253inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueContain(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1254{
1255 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value)) {
1256 if (downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value).valueID() == CSSValueNone)
1257 return builderState.style().setContain(RenderStyle::initialContainment());
1258 if (downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value).valueID() == CSSValueStrict)
1259 return builderState.style().setContain(RenderStyle::strictContainment());
1260 return builderState.style().setContain(RenderStyle::contentContainment());
1261 }
1262
1263 if (!is<CSSValueList>(value))
1264 return;
1265
1266 OptionSet<Containment> containment;
1267 auto& list = downcast<CSSValueList>(value);
1268 for (auto& item : list) {
1269 auto& value = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get());
1270 switch (value.valueID()) {
1271 case CSSValueSize:
1272 containment.add(Containment::Size);
1273 break;
1274 case CSSValueLayout:
1275 containment.add(Containment::Layout);
1276 break;
1277 case CSSValuePaint:
1278 containment.add(Containment::Paint);
1279 break;
1280 default:
1281 break;
1282 };
1283 }
1284 return builderState.style().setContain(containment);
1285}

1287inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueWebkitTextEmphasisStyle(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1288{
1289 if (is<CSSValueList>(value)) {
1290 auto& list = downcast<CSSValueList>(value);
1291 ASSERT(list.length() == 2);
1292
1293 for (auto& item : list) {
1294 CSSPrimitiveValue& value = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get());
1295 if (value.valueID() == CSSValueFilled || value.valueID() == CSSValueOpen)
1296 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisFill(value);
1297 else
1298 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisMark(value);
1299 }
1300 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisCustomMark(nullAtom());
1301 return;
1302 }
1303
1304 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
1305 if (primitiveValue.isString()) {
1306 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisFill(TextEmphasisFill::Filled);
1307 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisMark(TextEmphasisMark::Custom);
1308 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisCustomMark(primitiveValue.stringValue());
1309 return;
1310 }
1311
1312 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisCustomMark(nullAtom());
1313
1314 if (primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueFilled || primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueOpen) {
1315 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisFill(primitiveValue);
1316 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisMark(TextEmphasisMark::Auto);
1317 } else {
1318 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisFill(TextEmphasisFill::Filled);
1319 builderState.style().setTextEmphasisMark(primitiveValue);
1320 }

1323template <BuilderCustom::CounterBehavior counterBehavior>
1324inline void BuilderCustom::applyInheritCounter(BuilderState& builderState)
1325{
1326 auto& map = builderState.style().accessCounterDirectives();
1327 for (auto& keyValue : const_cast<RenderStyle&>(builderState.parentStyle()).accessCounterDirectives()) {
1328 auto& directives = map.add(keyValue.key, CounterDirectives { }).iterator->value;
1329 if (counterBehavior == Reset)
1330 directives.resetValue = keyValue.value.resetValue;
1331 else
1332 directives.incrementValue = keyValue.value.incrementValue;
1333 }
1334}
1335
1336template <BuilderCustom::CounterBehavior counterBehavior>
1337inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueCounter(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1338{
1339 bool setCounterIncrementToNone = counterBehavior == Increment && is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value) && downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value).valueID() == CSSValueNone;
1340
1341 if (!is<CSSValueList>(value) && !setCounterIncrementToNone)
1342 return;
1343
1344 CounterDirectiveMap& map = builderState.style().accessCounterDirectives();
1345 for (auto& keyValue : map) {
1346 if (counterBehavior == Reset)
1347 keyValue.value.resetValue = std::nullopt;
1348 else
1349 keyValue.value.incrementValue = std::nullopt;
1350 }
1351
1352 if (setCounterIncrementToNone)
1353 return;
1354
1355 for (auto& item : downcast<CSSValueList>(value)) {
1356 Pair* pair = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get()).pairValue();
1357 AtomString identifier = pair->first()->stringValue();
1358 int value = pair->second()->intValue();
1359 auto& directives = map.add(identifier, CounterDirectives { }).iterator->value;
1360 if (counterBehavior == Reset)
1361 directives.resetValue = value;
1362 else
1363 directives.incrementValue = saturatedSum<int>(directives.incrementValue.value_or(0), value);
1364 }
1365}

1403inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueCursor(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1404{
1405 builderState.style().clearCursorList();
1406 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value)) {
1407 CursorType cursor = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
1408 if (builderState.style().cursor() != cursor)
1409 builderState.style().setCursor(cursor);
1410 return;
1411 }
1412
1413 builderState.style().setCursor(CursorType::Auto);
1414 auto& list = downcast<CSSValueList>(value);
1415 for (auto& item : list) {
1416 if (is<CSSCursorImageValue>(item)) {
1417 auto& image = downcast<CSSCursorImageValue>(item.get());
1418 builderState.style().addCursor(builderState.createStyleImage(image), image.hotSpot());
1419 continue;
1420 }
1421
1422 builderState.style().setCursor(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get()));
1423 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(item.ptr() == list.item(list.length() - 1), "Cursor ID fallback should always be last in the list");
1424 return;
1425 }

1442inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueFill(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1443{
1444 auto& svgStyle = builderState.style().accessSVGStyle();
1445 const auto* localValue = value.isPrimitiveValue() ? &downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value) : nullptr;
1446 String url;
1447 if (value.isValueList()) {
1448 const CSSValueList& list = downcast<CSSValueList>(value);
1449 url = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(list.item(0))->stringValue();
1450 localValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(list.item(1));
1451 }
1452
1453 if (!localValue)
1454 return;
1455
1456 Color color;
1457 auto paintType = SVGPaintType::RGBColor;
1458 if (localValue->isURI()) {
1459 paintType = SVGPaintType::URI;
1460 url = localValue->stringValue();
1461 } else if (localValue->isValueID() && localValue->valueID() == CSSValueNone)
1462 paintType = url.isEmpty() ? SVGPaintType::None : SVGPaintType::URINone;
1463 else if (localValue->isValueID() && localValue->valueID() == CSSValueCurrentcolor) {
1464 color = builderState.style().color();
1465 paintType = url.isEmpty() ? SVGPaintType::CurrentColor : SVGPaintType::URICurrentColor;
1466 } else {
1467 color = builderState.colorFromPrimitiveValue(*localValue);
1468 paintType = url.isEmpty() ? SVGPaintType::RGBColor : SVGPaintType::URIRGBColor;
1469 }
1470 svgStyle.setFillPaint(paintType, color, url, builderState.applyPropertyToRegularStyle(), builderState.applyPropertyToVisitedLinkStyle());
1471}

1521
1522inline void BuilderCustom::applyInheritContent(BuilderState&)
1523{
1524 // FIXME: In CSS3, it will be possible to inherit content. In CSS2 it is not. This
1525 // note is a reminder that eventually "inherit" needs to be supported.
1526}
1527
1528inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueContent(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1529{
1530 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value)) {
1531 const auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
1532 ASSERT_UNUSED(primitiveValue, primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueNormal || primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueNone);
1533 builderState.style().clearContent();
1534 return;
1535 }
1536
1537 bool didSet = false;
1538 for (auto& item : downcast<CSSValueList>(value)) {
1539 if (is<CSSImageGeneratorValue>(item)) {
1540 if (is<CSSGradientValue>(item))
1541 builderState.style().setContent(StyleGeneratedImage::create(downcast<CSSGradientValue>(builderState.resolveImageStyles(item.get()).get())), didSet);
1542 else
1543 builderState.style().setContent(StyleGeneratedImage::create(downcast<CSSImageGeneratorValue>(builderState.resolveImageStyles(item.get()).get())), didSet);
1544 didSet = true;
1545 }
1546
1547 if (is<CSSImageSetValue>(item)) {
1548 builderState.style().setContent(StyleImageSet::create(downcast<CSSImageSetValue>(builderState.resolveImageStyles(item.get()).get())), didSet);
1549 didSet = true;
1550 }
1551
1552 if (is<CSSImageValue>(item)) {
1553 builderState.style().setContent(StyleCachedImage::create(downcast<CSSImageValue>(builderState.resolveImageStyles(item.get()).get())), didSet);
1554 didSet = true;
1555 continue;
1556 }
1557
1558 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item))
1559 continue;
1560
1561 auto& contentValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get());
1562 if (contentValue.isString()) {
1563 builderState.style().setContent(contentValue.stringValue().impl(), didSet);
1564 didSet = true;
1565 } else if (contentValue.isAttr()) {
1566 // FIXME: Can a namespace be specified for an attr(foo)?
1567 if (builderState.style().styleType() == PseudoId::None)
1568 builderState.style().setHasAttrContent();
1569 else
1570 const_cast<RenderStyle&>(builderState.parentStyle()).setHasAttrContent();
1571 QualifiedName attr(nullAtom(), contentValue.stringValue().impl(), nullAtom());
1572 const AtomString& value = builderState.element() ? builderState.element()->getAttribute(attr) : nullAtom();
1573 builderState.style().setContent(value.isNull() ? emptyAtom() : value.impl(), didSet);
1574 didSet = true;
1575 // Register the fact that the attribute value affects the style.
1576 builderState.registerContentAttribute(attr.localName());
1577 } else if (contentValue.isCounter()) {
1578 auto* counterValue = contentValue.counterValue();
1579 ListStyleType listStyleType = ListStyleType::None;
1580 CSSValueID listStyleIdent = counterValue->listStyleIdent();
1581 if (listStyleIdent != CSSValueNone)
1582 listStyleType = static_cast<ListStyleType>(listStyleIdent - CSSValueDisc);
1583 auto counter = makeUnique<CounterContent>(counterValue->identifier(), listStyleType, counterValue->separator());
1584 builderState.style().setContent(WTFMove(counter), didSet);
1585 didSet = true;
1586 } else {
1587 switch (contentValue.valueID()) {
1588 case CSSValueOpenQuote:
1589 builderState.style().setContent(QuoteType::OpenQuote, didSet);
1590 didSet = true;
1591 break;
1592 case CSSValueCloseQuote:
1593 builderState.style().setContent(QuoteType::CloseQuote, didSet);
1594 didSet = true;
1595 break;
1596 case CSSValueNoOpenQuote:
1597 builderState.style().setContent(QuoteType::NoOpenQuote, didSet);
1598 didSet = true;
1599 break;
1600 case CSSValueNoCloseQuote:
1601 builderState.style().setContent(QuoteType::NoCloseQuote, didSet);
1602 didSet = true;
1603 break;
1604 default:
1605 // normal and none do not have any effect.
1606 break;
1607 }
1608 }
1609 }
1610 if (!didSet)
1611 builderState.style().clearContent();
1612}

1734// When the CSS keyword "larger" is used, this function will attempt to match within the keyword
1735// table, and failing that, will simply multiply by 1.2.
1736inline float BuilderCustom::largerFontSize(float size)
1737{
1738 // FIXME: Figure out where we fall in the size ranges (xx-small to xxx-large) and scale up to
1739 // the next size level.
1740 return size * 1.2f;
1741}

1743// Like the previous function, but for the keyword "smaller".
1744inline float BuilderCustom::smallerFontSize(float size)
1745{
1746 // FIXME: Figure out where we fall in the size ranges (xx-small to xxx-large) and scale down to
1747 // the next size level.
1748 return size / 1.2f;
1749}
1750
1751inline float BuilderCustom::determineRubyTextSizeMultiplier(BuilderState& builderState)
1752{
1753 if (builderState.style().rubyPosition() != RubyPosition::InterCharacter)
1754 return 0.5f;
1755
1756 // FIXME: This hack is to ensure tone marks are the same size as
1757 // the bopomofo. This code will go away if we make a special renderer
1758 // for the tone marks eventually.
1759 if (auto* element = builderState.element()) {
1760 for (auto& ancestor : ancestorsOfType<HTMLElement>(*element)) {
1761 if (ancestor.hasTagName(HTMLNames::rtTag))
1762 return 1.0f;
1763 }
1764 }
1765 return 0.25f;
1766}

1793inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueFontSize(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1794{
1795 auto fontDescription = builderState.fontDescription();
1796 fontDescription.setKeywordSizeFromIdentifier(CSSValueInvalid);
1797
1798 float parentSize = builderState.parentStyle().fontDescription().specifiedSize();
1799 bool parentIsAbsoluteSize = builderState.parentStyle().fontDescription().isAbsoluteSize();
1800
1801 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
1802 float size;
1803 if (CSSValueID ident = primitiveValue.valueID()) {
1804 fontDescription.setIsAbsoluteSize(parentIsAbsoluteSize && (ident == CSSValueLarger || ident == CSSValueSmaller || ident == CSSValueWebkitRubyText));
1805
1806 // Keywords are being used.
1807 switch (ident) {
1808 case CSSValueXxSmall:
1809 case CSSValueXSmall:
1810 case CSSValueSmall:
1811 case CSSValueMedium:
1812 case CSSValueLarge:
1813 case CSSValueXLarge:
1814 case CSSValueXxLarge:
1815 case CSSValueWebkitXxxLarge:
1816 size = Style::fontSizeForKeyword(ident, fontDescription.useFixedDefaultSize(), builderState.document());
1817 fontDescription.setKeywordSizeFromIdentifier(ident);
1818 break;
1819 case CSSValueLarger:
1820 size = largerFontSize(parentSize);
1821 break;
1822 case CSSValueSmaller:
1823 size = smallerFontSize(parentSize);
1824 break;
1825 case CSSValueWebkitRubyText:
1826 size = determineRubyTextSizeMultiplier(builderState) * parentSize;
1827 break;
1828 default:
1829 return;
1830 }
1831 } else {
1832 fontDescription.setIsAbsoluteSize(parentIsAbsoluteSize || !(primitiveValue.isPercentage() || primitiveValue.isFontRelativeLength()));
1833 if (primitiveValue.isLength()) {
1834 CSSToLengthConversionData conversionData { &builderState.parentStyle(), builderState.rootElementStyle(), &builderState.parentStyle(), builderState.document().renderView(), 1.0f, CSSPropertyFontSize, &builderState.style() };
1835 size = primitiveValue.computeLength<float>(conversionData);
1836 } else if (primitiveValue.isPercentage())
1837 size = (primitiveValue.floatValue() * parentSize) / 100.0f;
1838 else if (primitiveValue.isCalculatedPercentageWithLength()) {
1839 // FIXME: Why does this need a different root style than the isLength case above?
1840 CSSToLengthConversionData conversionData { &builderState.parentStyle(), builderState.cssToLengthConversionData().rootStyle(), &builderState.parentStyle(), builderState.document().renderView(), 1.0f, CSSPropertyFontSize, &builderState.style() };
1841 size = primitiveValue.cssCalcValue()->createCalculationValue(conversionData)->evaluate(parentSize);
1842 } else
1843 return;
1844 }
1845
1846 if (size < 0)
1847 return;
1848
1849 builderState.setFontSize(fontDescription, std::min(maximumAllowedFontSize, size));
1850 builderState.setFontDescription(WTFMove(fontDescription));
1851}

1963void BuilderCustom::applyValueAlt(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1964{
1965 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value);
1966 if (primitiveValue.isString())
1967 builderState.style().setContentAltText(primitiveValue.stringValue());
1968 else if (primitiveValue.isAttr()) {
1969 // FIXME: Can a namespace be specified for an attr(foo)?
1970 if (builderState.style().styleType() == PseudoId::None)
1971 builderState.style().setUnique();
1972 else
1973 const_cast<RenderStyle&>(builderState.parentStyle()).setUnique();
1974
1975 QualifiedName attr(nullAtom(), primitiveValue.stringValue(), nullAtom());
1976 const AtomString& value = builderState.element() ? builderState.element()->getAttribute(attr) : nullAtom();
1977 builderState.style().setContentAltText(value.isNull() ? emptyAtom() : value);
1978
1979 // Register the fact that the attribute value affects the style.
1980 builderState.registerContentAttribute(attr.localName());
1981 } else
1982 builderState.style().setContentAltText(emptyAtom());
1983}

1985inline void BuilderCustom::applyValueWillChange(BuilderState& builderState, CSSValue& value)
1986{
1987 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value)) {
1988 ASSERT(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value).valueID() == CSSValueAuto);
1989 builderState.style().setWillChange(nullptr);
1990 return;
1991 }
1992
1993 auto willChange = WillChangeData::create();
1994 for (auto& item : downcast<CSSValueList>(value)) {
1995 if (!is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item))
1996 continue;
1997 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(item.get());
1998 switch (primitiveValue.valueID()) {
1999 case CSSValueScrollPosition:
2000 willChange->addFeature(WillChangeData::Feature::ScrollPosition);
2001 break;
2002 case CSSValueContents:
2003 willChange->addFeature(WillChangeData::Feature::Contents);
2004 break;
2005 default:
2006 if (primitiveValue.isPropertyID()) {
2007 if (primitiveValue.propertyID() == CSSPropertyContain && !builderState.document().settings().cssContainmentEnabled())
2008 break;
2009 willChange->addFeature(WillChangeData::Feature::Property, primitiveValue.propertyID());
2010 }
2011 break;
2012 }
2013 }
2014 builderState.style().setWillChange(WTFMove(willChange));
2015}
